title: Delaware's Nadjah Nicole back on 'The Voice' Tuesday

Delaware singer Nadjah Nicole is set to return to national television Tuesday night on NBC's "The Voice." (Photo: NBC/Paul Drinkwater) 
A month after wowing judges on the season premiere of "The Voice," Delaware singer Nadjah Nicole is set to return to national television Tuesday night. 
The 23-year-old faces her first singing battle on the NBC reality show Tuesday at 9. 
Nicole , who is coached by country singer and Big Barrel Country Music Festival alum Blake Shelton, will be advised by fellow country king Brad Paisley. Delaware's Nadjah Nicole wows 'The Voice' 
The Claymont-based singer is slated to battle fellow contestant Cole Criske by singing Britney Spears' "One More Time." 
Nicole is fresh from her headlining gig earlier this month at World Cafe Live at the Queen's downstairs stage in Wilmington, which she helped preview as a guest on The News Journal's pop culture podcast, "Hi, I'm in Delaware!" 
A single mother of one, Nicole works as a personal banker at WSFS. Podcast: 'The Voice' singer Nadjah Nicole sits in! 
Nicole won rave reviews on her national TV debut from the show's coaches -- Maroon 5's Adam Levine said he was "blown away," Gwen Stefani said "it was incredible" and Shelton said she "sounded like a star." Now the pressure is on to keep them on her side. 
Fans of the show seem to be drawn Nicole: her initial audition video from the show is nearing 1 million views.
